
00:00:03,041 --> 00:00:04,042
( <i>grunts</i> )

00:00:17,923 --> 00:00:19,224
CURTIS:
<i>Stacy Vollmer was last seen</i>

00:00:19,291 --> 00:00:22,160
<i>practicing alone</i>
<i>on the school tennis court</i>

00:00:22,227 --> 00:00:24,196
<i>that Friday at around 9:00 p.m.</i>

00:00:26,865 --> 00:00:30,769
<i>The clothes she was wearing</i>
<i>were found in her locker.</i>

00:00:39,378 --> 00:00:42,481
<i>Her body was discovered</i>
<i>near the football field</i>

00:00:42,548 --> 00:00:46,385
<i>by the landscaping crew</i>
<i>the following Monday morning.</i>

00:00:49,488 --> 00:00:51,323
Can you tell us
the exact location of the body?

00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:54,927
She was dumped in a flower bed,
wrapped in a shower curtain.

00:00:54,993 --> 00:00:56,995
( <i>sirens blaring</i> )

00:00:57,062 --> 00:00:59,665
<i>CSI arrived an hour later,</i>

00:00:59,731 --> 00:01:01,967
<i>excavated the body</i>
<i>and began processing the</i>
<i>scene.</i>

00:01:06,638 --> 00:01:08,707
SINCLAIR:
<i>Dr. Robbins, can you tell us</i>
<i>how Stacy died?</i>

00:01:08,774 --> 00:01:11,276
ROBBINS:
<i>Beneath this laceration,</i>

00:01:11,343 --> 00:01:14,279
I found a complex fracture
of the occipital bone.

00:01:14,346 --> 00:01:18,250
Multiple shards of bone were
driven into the occipital lobe

00:01:18,317 --> 00:01:19,751
of the brain,

00:01:19,818 --> 00:01:21,086
resulting in massive bleeding.

00:01:21,153 --> 00:01:25,457
The cause of death was
cerebral hemorrhage,

00:01:25,524 --> 00:01:27,426
consistent with a single,
sharp blow to her head.

00:01:34,867 --> 00:01:36,969
A search of the
defendant's home

00:01:37,035 --> 00:01:39,137
yielded a
laundry hamper

00:01:39,204 --> 00:01:40,305
containing the
clothes he wore

00:01:40,372 --> 00:01:41,306
the night of
the murder.

00:01:41,373 --> 00:01:42,808
SINCLAIR:
Did you find any blood

00:01:42,875 --> 00:01:44,910
or DNA on the clothes?

00:01:44,977 --> 00:01:46,845
No. We determined
they had been bleached.

00:01:46,912 --> 00:01:51,016
Isn't bleach used to destroy
blood and DNA evidence?

00:01:51,083 --> 00:01:53,118
Objection: argumentative.
SINCLAIR:
Withdrawn.

00:01:53,185 --> 00:01:55,087
What else did you find
in the house?

00:01:55,153 --> 00:01:57,623
Human hairs consistent
with the victim

00:01:57,689 --> 00:02:01,159
were discovered in the drain
of the bathroom sink.

00:02:01,226 --> 00:02:02,594
DNA was extracted

00:02:02,661 --> 00:02:04,963
and was also matched
to the victim.

00:02:05,030 --> 00:02:08,467
And based on this evidence,
police arrested Marlon West.

00:02:09,501 --> 00:02:11,103
That's correct.

00:02:11,169 --> 00:02:12,938
SINCLAIR:
Thank you, Mr. Stokes.

00:02:13,005 --> 00:02:15,340
No further questions.

00:02:16,542 --> 00:02:19,044
The State now calls Hannah West.

00:02:19,111 --> 00:02:20,312
ALLRED:
Your Honor,

00:02:20,379 --> 00:02:21,680
defense reiterates
our objection.

00:02:21,747 --> 00:02:23,382
She's a 12-year-old girl.

00:02:23,448 --> 00:02:26,018
JUDGE:
We've been through
this already, counsel.

00:02:26,084 --> 00:02:28,987
The defendant's sister is being
called as a hostile witness.

00:02:29,054 --> 00:02:31,156
That means the district attorney
is permitted

00:02:31,223 --> 00:02:33,125
to ask leading
questions.

00:02:33,192 --> 00:02:34,726
Be nice.

00:02:43,969 --> 00:02:46,138
Now, Hannah,
isn't it a fact

00:02:46,205 --> 00:02:49,975
that on the night
of Friday, December 2, 2005,

00:02:50,042 --> 00:02:52,377
your parents left you
and your brother,

00:02:52,444 --> 00:02:54,146
the defendant,
home alone?

00:02:54,213 --> 00:02:55,480
They went away for a...

00:02:55,547 --> 00:02:56,548
Yes or no, please.

00:02:56,615 --> 00:02:58,050
Yes.

00:02:58,116 --> 00:02:59,985
SINCLAIR:
And isn't it
also a fact

00:03:00,052 --> 00:03:01,887
that you and your
brother were not together

00:03:01,954 --> 00:03:04,756
between the hours
of 6:00 and 10:00 p.m.?

00:03:04,823 --> 00:03:06,825
Well, Marlon--
he didn't really...

00:03:06,892 --> 00:03:08,026
Yes or no?

00:03:08,093 --> 00:03:09,895
Yes.

00:03:09,962 --> 00:03:10,896
SINCLAIR:
Thank you, Hannah.

00:03:10,963 --> 00:03:13,031
I'd like to say something...

00:03:13,098 --> 00:03:14,266
No further questions,
Your Honor.

00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:15,701
Cross-examination?

00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:17,669
Absolutely, Your Honor.

00:03:17,736 --> 00:03:19,705
Uh, Hannah,

00:03:19,771 --> 00:03:21,240
wh-what were
you trying to say?

00:03:21,306 --> 00:03:22,741
Objection:
calls for a narrative.

00:03:22,808 --> 00:03:23,876
Overruled.

00:03:23,942 --> 00:03:25,444
ALLRED:
You go ahead, Hannah.

00:03:25,511 --> 00:03:26,812
You say
what you need to say.

00:03:29,281 --> 00:03:32,351
Marlon didn't kill Stacy.

00:03:32,417 --> 00:03:36,889
( <i>crowd murmuring</i> )

00:03:36,955 --> 00:03:38,090
I did.

00:03:41,326 --> 00:03:43,962
And I was wearing this
when I did it.

00:03:54,673 --> 00:03:57,342
♪ ♪

00:03:57,409 --> 00:03:59,645
♪ ♪

00:03:59,711 --> 00:04:01,375
♪ ♪

00:04:01,375 --> 00:04:04,383
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:04:04,449 --> 00:04:07,786
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:04:07,853 --> 00:04:10,556
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:04:10,622 --> 00:04:12,324
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:04:12,391 --> 00:04:13,825
♪ I really wanna know ♪

00:04:13,892 --> 00:04:16,895
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:04:16,962 --> 00:04:18,130
♪ Oh-oh-oh ♪
♪ Who... ♪

00:04:18,197 --> 00:04:22,000
♪ Come on, tell me who are you,
you, you ♪

00:04:22,067 --> 00:04:25,337
♪ Oh, you! ♪

00:04:27,498 --> 00:04:29,997
Good news is Judge
Crawford denied

00:04:29,997 --> 00:04:31,765
the defense's
motion to dismiss.

00:04:31,832 --> 00:04:32,933
Of course he did.

00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,101
She's just a mixed-up kid

00:04:34,168 --> 00:04:35,436
trying to protect
her older brother.

00:04:35,502 --> 00:04:37,438
All the evidence
points to Marlon.

00:04:37,504 --> 00:04:39,106
Yeah, and all the jury's
going to remember

00:04:39,173 --> 00:04:40,607
is a little girl
in a bloody shirt

00:04:40,674 --> 00:04:41,775
confessing to murder.

00:04:41,842 --> 00:04:44,178
That's reasonable doubt
on a silver platter.

00:04:44,244 --> 00:04:45,446
All right, then we have to prove

00:04:45,512 --> 00:04:46,814
that Hannah could not
have done this.

00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,349
Exactly.

00:04:48,415 --> 00:04:50,084
We'll need a week
to reexamine the evidence.

00:04:50,150 --> 00:04:52,019
Judge gave the D.A.
a 72-hour continuance.

00:04:52,086 --> 00:04:53,620
Come on...
Best he could
do, Nick.

00:04:53,687 --> 00:04:56,190
Now you go do your best.

00:05:30,858 --> 00:05:33,227
MARLON:
<i>Everybody thought</i>
<i>Stacy was so...</i>

00:05:33,293 --> 00:05:34,928
special.

00:05:34,995 --> 00:05:36,764
She thought so, too.

00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:38,432
She wasn't.

00:05:38,499 --> 00:05:41,769
Stacy was a stuck-up bitch
and a miserable person.

00:05:41,835 --> 00:05:43,771
I just put her
out of her misery.

00:05:43,837 --> 00:05:45,939
( <i>sighs</i> )

00:05:46,006 --> 00:05:48,642
I killed her and I put her
in the ground.

00:05:48,709 --> 00:05:50,744
That's all I've got to say.

00:05:52,513 --> 00:05:54,114
The judge suppressed
the video

00:05:54,181 --> 00:05:56,283
because a child advocate
was never brought in,

00:05:56,350 --> 00:05:58,819
even though Marlon
had waived his rights.

00:05:58,886 --> 00:06:00,654
We really didn't need
a confession out of him.

00:06:00,721 --> 00:06:02,523
The case against this kid
was solid.

00:06:03,557 --> 00:06:05,726
<i>It started out as a prank:</i>

00:06:05,793 --> 00:06:08,362
<i>a sabotaged showerhead.</i>

00:06:08,429 --> 00:06:10,931
( <i>explosion</i> )
( <i>shrieking</i> )

00:06:10,998 --> 00:06:14,068
PH tests later revealed
the presence

00:06:14,134 --> 00:06:15,069
of a strong
base substance

00:06:15,135 --> 00:06:17,004
which was
later identified

00:06:17,071 --> 00:06:18,739
as sodium hydroxide.

00:06:18,806 --> 00:06:19,740
Sounds like Marlon packed

00:06:19,807 --> 00:06:21,241
the showerhead
with elemental sodium.

00:06:21,308 --> 00:06:22,743
A high school chemistry
favorite, yeah.

00:06:22,810 --> 00:06:24,378
Just add water,
and instant kaboom.

00:06:24,445 --> 00:06:25,913
BROWN:
Those out-of-order signs

00:06:25,979 --> 00:06:28,015
must've been part
of his game.

00:06:28,082 --> 00:06:31,552
You funnel the victim
to the right showerhead.

00:06:31,618 --> 00:06:32,753
Did you process these?

00:06:32,820 --> 00:06:34,922
Yeah, I matched
the spindle marks on the paper

00:06:34,988 --> 00:06:36,056
to a laser printer

00:06:36,123 --> 00:06:37,591
in the high
school library.

00:06:37,658 --> 00:06:39,093
Accessible to any student.

00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:40,728
Mm-hmm.

00:06:40,794 --> 00:06:43,063
"Multiple fragments of metal
penetrating the skin and dermis

00:06:43,130 --> 00:06:46,233
"as deep as
the superficial musculature

00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:48,035
of the back
and neck."

00:06:48,102 --> 00:06:49,937
The showerhead explosion
didn't kill her.

00:06:50,004 --> 00:06:51,472
No, no, it did not.

00:06:51,538 --> 00:06:53,974
What happened
to the shower curtain?

00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:55,376
STOKES:
Well, the vic was injured,

00:06:55,442 --> 00:06:56,610
disoriented.

00:06:56,677 --> 00:06:59,113
She grabbed the first thing
she could to cover up and ran.

00:06:59,179 --> 00:07:01,048
( <i>shrieking</i> )

00:07:01,115 --> 00:07:04,518
STOKES:
<i>The intermittent blood trail</i>
<i>started in the locker room</i>

00:07:04,585 --> 00:07:05,786
<i>and headed down a hall.</i>

00:07:07,321 --> 00:07:09,823
So Marlon followed her out
just to hear her squeal?

00:07:09,890 --> 00:07:11,759
Or chased her out, yeah.

00:07:11,825 --> 00:07:13,160
There's no way
to know.

00:07:13,227 --> 00:07:14,962
Either way, she ended up
at the bottom of the stairs.

00:07:15,029 --> 00:07:16,597
The size of the blood pool

00:07:16,664 --> 00:07:19,133
indicates that the fatal wound
occurred there.

00:07:19,199 --> 00:07:20,401
Do you have
any physical evidence

00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:22,903
that would conclusively rule
Hannah out as a suspect?

00:07:22,970 --> 00:07:27,274
Well, yeah-- she's
four-foot-three and 65 pounds.

00:07:27,341 --> 00:07:30,411
The crime just required
more strength than she's got.

00:07:30,477 --> 00:07:32,579
How old is she?

00:07:32,646 --> 00:07:33,947
Twelve.

00:07:34,815 --> 00:07:35,949
In high school?

00:07:36,016 --> 00:07:37,851
She's a high school senior.

00:07:37,918 --> 00:07:39,953
She skipped
six grades.

00:07:40,020 --> 00:07:41,121
She's a prodigy.

00:07:41,188 --> 00:07:44,525
Which means she has the brains
for murder.

00:07:44,591 --> 00:07:45,759
Yeah, but not the brawn.

00:07:45,826 --> 00:07:47,828
The body was moved
from the high school building

00:07:47,895 --> 00:07:49,797
across a
football field

00:07:49,863 --> 00:07:50,931
and then hastily buried.

00:07:50,998 --> 00:07:54,268
The vic's car was then driven
two miles from campus

00:07:54,335 --> 00:07:56,036
and parked in front of the house
of a kid named

00:07:56,103 --> 00:07:58,372
Scott Baird,
Stacy's boyfriend--

00:07:58,439 --> 00:08:00,374
I think possibly to frame him.

00:08:00,441 --> 00:08:01,975
Was he ever a suspect?

00:08:02,042 --> 00:08:03,210
No. He plays varsity hoops.

00:08:03,277 --> 00:08:05,312
He was out of town
on an away game.

00:08:05,379 --> 00:08:07,715
I found blades of grass

00:08:07,781 --> 00:08:09,950
with blood on them
near the vic's car--

00:08:10,017 --> 00:08:12,486
nondescript tracks
headed towards

00:08:12,553 --> 00:08:13,587
the next-door
neighbor's house.

00:08:13,654 --> 00:08:14,822
Marlon West.

00:08:14,888 --> 00:08:16,390
Yeah. This kid's been
in trouble before.

00:08:16,457 --> 00:08:17,725
Multiple fights, threats.

00:08:17,791 --> 00:08:20,461
It just got out
of hand this time.

00:08:20,527 --> 00:08:23,831
Marlon West
killed Stacy Vollmer.

00:08:23,897 --> 00:08:27,901
His little sister's just trying
to exonerate him.

00:08:58,432 --> 00:08:59,867
♪ ♪

00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:31,398
Hey, Nick.

00:09:31,465 --> 00:09:32,900
Hodges, did you get
the soil analysis back

00:09:32,966 --> 00:09:34,068
on Hannah's shirt?

00:09:34,134 --> 00:09:36,103
Matches the site
of the body dump.
Really!

00:09:36,170 --> 00:09:39,239
So does this make
Doogie Howser-ette your killer?

00:09:39,306 --> 00:09:40,741
Uh, I kind of doubt it.

00:09:40,808 --> 00:09:43,344
Don't be so sure. It's not easy.

00:09:44,378 --> 00:09:46,714
What isn't easy, Hodges?

00:09:46,780 --> 00:09:48,882
Being profoundly gifted,

00:09:48,949 --> 00:09:50,984
knowing that everybody
knows that you're always

00:09:51,051 --> 00:09:51,985
ten steps ahead of them.

00:09:52,052 --> 00:09:53,320
It's a lot of pressure.

00:09:53,387 --> 00:09:54,988
Some days, you feel

00:09:55,055 --> 00:09:56,256
like you're just
going to snap.

00:09:56,323 --> 00:09:57,825
I know the feeling.

00:09:57,891 --> 00:10:00,995
SIDLE:
<i>In his confession,</i>

00:10:01,061 --> 00:10:03,497
Marlon basically said
that Stacy deserved to die.

00:10:03,564 --> 00:10:05,566
He was alone
in that opinion.

00:10:05,632 --> 00:10:08,302
Everybody loved Stacy--
parents and students.

00:10:08,369 --> 00:10:12,506
4.0 GPA, varsity tennis
team, homecoming queen.

00:10:12,573 --> 00:10:14,608
She even took a public
virginity pledge

00:10:14,675 --> 00:10:16,710
with some of
her classmates.

00:10:16,777 --> 00:10:18,645
Did they have those
in your high school?

00:10:18,712 --> 00:10:20,080
No.

00:10:20,147 --> 00:10:21,648
Do you believe
that Marlon killed her?

00:10:21,715 --> 00:10:23,550
I was looking
right into his eyes

00:10:23,617 --> 00:10:25,285
when he told
me he did it.

00:10:25,352 --> 00:10:28,288
There's no doubt
in my mind.

00:10:28,355 --> 00:10:31,025
CURTIS:
Two confessions,
one crime.

00:10:31,091 --> 00:10:33,927
We don't get
that a lot.

00:10:33,994 --> 00:10:35,929
When did you last
speak with Marlon?

00:10:35,996 --> 00:10:39,099
The day the police came
to my house and arrested him.

00:10:39,166 --> 00:10:40,467
You don't visit him?

00:10:40,534 --> 00:10:42,503
My parents won't let me
see him in jail.

00:10:42,569 --> 00:10:44,271
Bad environment.

00:10:44,338 --> 00:10:47,441
Marlon didn't put me up
to this.

00:10:47,508 --> 00:10:48,909
He was trying to protect me.

00:10:48,976 --> 00:10:51,211
It would've been wrong
to let him be punished

00:10:51,278 --> 00:10:52,946
for something I did.

00:10:55,983 --> 00:10:58,619
You don't think
I could have done it.

00:10:58,686 --> 00:11:00,254
Neither one of you.

00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:03,123
That's a big job
for a little girl.

00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:06,593
Not if you have
the right tools.

00:11:06,660 --> 00:11:10,764
Smart kid like you...
knows your brother's suffering.

00:11:10,831 --> 00:11:12,966
You feel bad,
you want to help,

00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:15,636
so you fabricate some evidence.

00:11:15,703 --> 00:11:17,671
If you thought
that the evidence was fake,

00:11:17,738 --> 00:11:19,473
I wouldn't still be in jail.

00:11:22,343 --> 00:11:25,145
Aren't you going to ask me
why I did it?

00:11:25,212 --> 00:11:27,047
Would you like to tell us?

00:11:29,083 --> 00:11:30,751
I throw off the curve.

00:11:30,818 --> 00:11:32,152
When I'm in a class,

00:11:32,219 --> 00:11:35,155
people who usually get A's,
suddenly get C's.

00:11:35,222 --> 00:11:37,491
Stacy was applying
to Harvard.

00:11:37,558 --> 00:11:40,094
She wanted me
to dumb myself down.

00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:41,996
I said no.

00:11:42,062 --> 00:11:44,131
She didn't like that.

00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:47,968
( <i>indistinct chatting</i> )

00:11:48,035 --> 00:11:50,804
Uh... babies use the wall dryer.

00:11:54,074 --> 00:11:56,143
( <i>laughter</i> )

00:11:58,879 --> 00:12:01,782
So you killed her
because she messed up your hair?

00:12:01,849 --> 00:12:03,517
No.

00:12:03,584 --> 00:12:05,386
I'm used to pranks like that.

00:12:05,452 --> 00:12:08,188
I get them most every day.

00:12:08,255 --> 00:12:10,524
But Stacy...
didn't stop there.

00:12:10,591 --> 00:12:13,794
She had to take it
to another level.

00:12:13,861 --> 00:12:16,196
And she used Scott to do it.

00:12:16,263 --> 00:12:18,465
Scott Baird, Stacy's boyfriend.

00:12:18,532 --> 00:12:22,036
I was his tutor.

00:12:22,102 --> 00:12:23,971
SCOTT:
You know,
I was really pissed off

00:12:24,038 --> 00:12:25,706
at Stacy when I heard
about the whole...

00:12:25,773 --> 00:12:28,008
hair dryer thing,

00:12:28,075 --> 00:12:30,177
but her... her friends
had put her up to it.

00:12:30,244 --> 00:12:32,446
Stacy wanted me
to give you something.

00:12:34,481 --> 00:12:36,150
It's a
peace offering.

00:12:36,216 --> 00:12:38,452
I think you'll look great
in it at the Spring Formal.

00:12:40,387 --> 00:12:42,189
Oh, you are so going.

00:12:44,258 --> 00:12:46,560
You like him.

00:12:46,627 --> 00:12:49,697
He's on the basketball team.

00:12:49,763 --> 00:12:51,365
I'm 12; I'm not allowed

00:12:51,432 --> 00:12:53,734
to like him, but...

00:12:53,801 --> 00:12:55,336
I went anyway.

00:12:55,402 --> 00:12:58,572
( <i>rock music playing</i> )

00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:08,215
Over here.

00:13:13,654 --> 00:13:15,789
( <i>laughing</i> )

00:13:15,856 --> 00:13:17,057
( <i>camera shutter clicks</i> )

00:13:17,124 --> 00:13:19,760
( <i>laughter</i> )

00:13:31,505 --> 00:13:33,707
The pictures were up
on MySpace that night.

00:13:33,774 --> 00:13:35,876
I got a ton of e-mails.

00:13:35,943 --> 00:13:38,112
