00:27:53,092 --> 00:27:54,560
Hey, guys.
Hey.

00:27:54,627 --> 00:27:56,863
This is Darcy,
my wife Tina's niece.
SIDLE:
Hi, Darcy.

00:27:56,929 --> 00:27:58,731
STOKES:
You were right; she's
about Hannah's size.

00:27:58,798 --> 00:28:01,634
More or less.
Stop talking about me.

00:28:01,701 --> 00:28:02,869
Hey, that's the best part!

00:28:02,935 --> 00:28:05,271
BROWN:
That's what
the pause button's for.

00:28:05,338 --> 00:28:07,373
It's time to work,
it's child labor day.

00:28:08,508 --> 00:28:09,609
Okay.

00:28:09,676 --> 00:28:11,644
Crime started
right here.

00:28:13,446 --> 00:28:14,814
( <i>explosion</i> )

00:28:14,881 --> 00:28:16,916
Think you could reach that?

00:28:21,521 --> 00:28:22,889
BROWN:
It's kind of hard
to sabotage

00:28:22,956 --> 00:28:24,290
a shower head you can't touch.

00:28:24,357 --> 00:28:26,859
STOKES:
Depends on what's
behind the curtain.

00:28:27,994 --> 00:28:28,995
Look at that.

00:28:31,397 --> 00:28:33,800
Just like the one
in Hannah's bathroom.

00:28:33,866 --> 00:28:35,268
Try this.

00:28:41,207 --> 00:28:43,643
SIDLE:
<i>Hannah had access</i>
<i>to the chem lab,</i>

00:28:43,710 --> 00:28:45,712
<i>and she knew</i>
<i>how to handle sodium...</i>

00:28:49,048 --> 00:28:51,684
( <i>explosion;</i>
<i>Stacy screaming</i> )

00:28:53,386 --> 00:28:56,022
SIDLE:
<i>Stacy would not have known</i>
<i>what hit her.</i>

00:28:56,089 --> 00:28:57,323
<i>Or where she was going.</i>

00:29:01,728 --> 00:29:02,895
( <i>screaming</i> )

00:29:08,835 --> 00:29:10,370
Stacy landed here
and bled out

00:29:10,436 --> 00:29:13,439
from the trauma
to her skull.

00:29:13,506 --> 00:29:15,642
Darcy, why don't you put
those headphones back on?

00:29:15,708 --> 00:29:18,011
Like I didn't hear
what you guys just said?

00:29:19,078 --> 00:29:21,114
Hannah could have done this.

00:29:21,180 --> 00:29:22,415
Maybe.

00:29:22,482 --> 00:29:25,118
But the next part,
that was the toughest.

00:29:25,184 --> 00:29:27,453
( <i>Darcy grunting</i> )

00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:28,888
DARCY:
It's too heavy!

00:29:28,955 --> 00:29:30,790
BROWN:
Come on, you're
almost there!

00:29:30,857 --> 00:29:32,191
It's building
character!

00:29:32,258 --> 00:29:34,093
SIDLE:
It's slow going,
but you're doing it.

00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:35,428
Yeah, so far.

00:29:35,495 --> 00:29:36,429
That's okay.

00:29:36,496 --> 00:29:38,298
Look, even if
she makes it to the grass,

00:29:38,364 --> 00:29:39,866
you think she could've
pulled the body

00:29:39,932 --> 00:29:41,301
the entire length
of the football field?

00:29:41,367 --> 00:29:43,603
There were scratches on
the shower curtain--

00:29:43,670 --> 00:29:45,738
the body was dragged
at least part of the way.

00:29:45,805 --> 00:29:48,474
SIDLE:
There's no way Hannah pulled it
the entire distance.

00:29:48,541 --> 00:29:50,276
Not by herself.

00:29:52,045 --> 00:29:53,846
They did it together.

00:29:53,913 --> 00:29:55,548
DARCY:
So...

00:29:55,615 --> 00:29:57,283
Did I help the dead girl?

00:30:02,237 --> 00:30:04,806
If Marlon and Hannah
committed this crime together,

00:30:04,873 --> 00:30:06,641
then they're probably
still working as a team.

00:30:06,708 --> 00:30:07,909
It's all part
of the plan:

00:30:07,976 --> 00:30:09,945
he confesses,
then she confesses.

00:30:10,011 --> 00:30:11,179
Muddy the waters enough,

00:30:11,246 --> 00:30:14,382
they both get off
on reasonable doubt.
Mm-hmm.

00:30:14,449 --> 00:30:16,785
Well, if we can't get
one to implicate the other,

00:30:16,851 --> 00:30:18,320
we're screwed.

00:30:20,088 --> 00:30:21,189
I don't get it.

00:30:21,256 --> 00:30:22,357
What's wrong with you people?

00:30:22,424 --> 00:30:24,492
You want me to confess?
Again?

00:30:24,559 --> 00:30:26,528
Fine, I will.

00:30:26,595 --> 00:30:27,562
Marlon, you need
to confirm

00:30:27,629 --> 00:30:29,030
that you're willing
to talk to me

00:30:29,097 --> 00:30:30,765
without a parent
or lawyer present,

00:30:30,832 --> 00:30:32,701
just a child advocate.

00:30:32,767 --> 00:30:34,369
I already said that was okay.

00:30:34,436 --> 00:30:36,671
I killed Stacy, what else
do I have to tell you?

00:30:36,738 --> 00:30:40,141
Well, the truth works for me.

00:30:40,208 --> 00:30:41,276
I like the truth.

00:30:41,343 --> 00:30:43,211
HANNAH:
<i>Look, I don't need a lawyer,</i>

00:30:43,278 --> 00:30:44,512
and I don't need my parents.

00:30:44,579 --> 00:30:46,248
I just want to do what's right.

00:30:46,314 --> 00:30:49,084
Hannah, taking the blame
for something you didn't do

00:30:49,150 --> 00:30:51,486
may be noble, but it
doesn't make it right.

00:30:51,553 --> 00:30:53,755
That's deep.

00:30:54,589 --> 00:30:55,523
Okay.

00:30:55,590 --> 00:30:56,725
It happened like this:

00:30:56,791 --> 00:30:59,561
Stacy humiliated me,
I wanted revenge.

00:30:59,628 --> 00:31:01,329
Yeah, and you knew that
there was no way you were ever

00:31:01,396 --> 00:31:02,330
going to get it by yourself.

00:31:02,397 --> 00:31:04,332
STOKES:
<i>You moved the body,</i>

00:31:04,399 --> 00:31:06,868
you buried it...

00:31:06,935 --> 00:31:08,470
I know I did; I was there.

00:31:08,536 --> 00:31:09,838
What's the problem?

00:31:09,905 --> 00:31:12,173
Well, the problem is what
happened in the locker room.

00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:13,842
I mean, you're not
the kind of guy

00:31:13,909 --> 00:31:16,811
who puts sodium in a shower head
to get back at somebody.

00:31:16,878 --> 00:31:18,313
You just trip them
in the hallway.

00:31:19,981 --> 00:31:22,584
So you think I'm too stupid
to have done it.

00:31:22,651 --> 00:31:24,419
Great, join the club.

00:31:24,486 --> 00:31:26,688
I don't think
you're stupid, Marlon,

00:31:26,755 --> 00:31:29,124
I didn't say you were stupid.

00:31:29,190 --> 00:31:31,393
But this is Hannah's game.

00:31:31,459 --> 00:31:32,894
The whole way.
Uh-uh.

00:31:32,961 --> 00:31:34,262
I broke into the chem lab.

00:31:34,329 --> 00:31:35,530
I stole the sodium.

00:31:35,597 --> 00:31:36,531
Me.

00:31:36,598 --> 00:31:37,666
All by myself.

00:31:37,732 --> 00:31:39,000
It takes skills

00:31:39,067 --> 00:31:40,569
to handle a chemical
like that properly.

00:31:40,635 --> 00:31:44,472
And, quite frankly, man,
you just don't have the skills.

00:31:44,539 --> 00:31:46,141
Your prank went bad,
and Stacy

00:31:46,207 --> 00:31:47,576
ended up dead.
That's what I said.

00:31:47,642 --> 00:31:49,044
Marlon helped you
bury her.

00:31:49,110 --> 00:31:50,312
No. Why won't you believe me?

00:31:50,378 --> 00:31:51,613
Marlon wasn't there.

00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:53,381
Stay away from Hannah.

00:31:53,448 --> 00:31:55,317
She had nothing to do
with this.

00:31:55,383 --> 00:31:59,054
No, no, she had everything
to do with this.

00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:00,155
You two were working together

00:32:00,221 --> 00:32:01,590
from the beginning.
Just leave her alone.

00:32:01,656 --> 00:32:03,058
SIDLE:
<i>Marlon helped you</i>
<i>move the body.</i>

00:32:03,124 --> 00:32:05,327
He didn't!
You expect me
to believe

00:32:05,393 --> 00:32:06,695
that a little girl like you

00:32:06,761 --> 00:32:08,196
lugged a hundred pounds
of dead weight

00:32:08,263 --> 00:32:09,464
the length of a football field

00:32:09,531 --> 00:32:11,466
by yourself?
No, of course not,

00:32:11,533 --> 00:32:13,268
that's why
I had to use the cart.

00:32:14,636 --> 00:32:15,804
What cart?

00:32:15,870 --> 00:32:16,838
The electric cart.

00:32:16,905 --> 00:32:18,673
The one the landscapers
were using.

00:32:18,740 --> 00:32:21,509
It was just sitting there,
right outside the door.

00:32:24,713 --> 00:32:28,116
( <i>computer mouse clicking</i> )

00:32:29,684 --> 00:32:31,620
( <i>computer beeps</i> )

00:32:34,656 --> 00:32:36,791
Wait a minute.

00:32:36,858 --> 00:32:38,460
I got something.

00:32:39,427 --> 00:32:42,697
Let me clean up this image.

00:32:48,737 --> 00:32:50,605
I see a cart, Sara.

00:32:55,243 --> 00:32:57,612
So Hannah could be telling
the truth.

00:32:57,679 --> 00:32:59,614
It's enough
for reasonable doubt.

00:32:59,681 --> 00:33:03,318
Great.
Thanks, Warrick.

00:33:03,385 --> 00:33:05,387
BROWN:
Yeah.

00:33:12,394 --> 00:33:13,428
STOKES:
<i>The evidence says</i>

00:33:13,495 --> 00:33:14,996
either one of them
could have done it,

00:33:15,063 --> 00:33:16,998
but I think
they were in it together.

00:33:17,065 --> 00:33:19,034
Okay, I'll proceed
against Marlon

00:33:19,100 --> 00:33:21,369
for the murder and bring charges
against Hannah

00:33:21,436 --> 00:33:22,370
for conspiracy.

00:33:22,437 --> 00:33:23,672
Another trial?

00:33:23,738 --> 00:33:25,473
You sure you want to go
through all this again?

00:33:25,540 --> 00:33:27,709
SINCLAIR:
Stacy's parents
and the community

00:33:27,776 --> 00:33:29,377
will have my ass if I don't.

00:33:29,444 --> 00:33:30,679
Well, then maybe
this is good news.

00:33:30,745 --> 00:33:32,113
I was just going
over Sofia's notes

00:33:32,180 --> 00:33:34,316
from the original
investigation.

00:33:34,382 --> 00:33:35,383
The night of the murder,

00:33:35,450 --> 00:33:37,118
Hannah and Marlon's parents
had left them alone

00:33:37,185 --> 00:33:38,787
in the house.

00:33:38,853 --> 00:33:42,190
A pizza was delivered to
the residence around 9:00 p.m.

00:33:42,257 --> 00:33:44,359
That's right around
Stacy's T.O.D.

00:33:44,426 --> 00:33:46,861
So, did anybody talk
to the delivery guy?

00:33:46,928 --> 00:33:48,863
Yes, and at the point that
Sofia did, a month had passed.

00:33:48,930 --> 00:33:50,632
Now, the delivery guy's
at the house all the time.

00:33:50,699 --> 00:33:53,034
He recognized photos
of both kids,

00:33:53,101 --> 00:33:56,805
but he could not be sure
which one answered

00:33:56,871 --> 00:33:57,806
the door that night.

00:33:57,872 --> 00:34:00,275
But one of them
did answer the door.

00:34:01,343 --> 00:34:02,978
So that means
they were not together

00:34:03,044 --> 00:34:04,412
at the time Stacy was killed.

00:34:04,479 --> 00:34:05,814
Yeah. So much for conspiracy.

00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:07,949
We're right back
where we started.

00:34:08,016 --> 00:34:09,150
Where we are is in the crapper.

00:34:09,217 --> 00:34:10,485
Look, I have to disclose
the cart.

00:34:10,552 --> 00:34:12,320
Defense is going
to eat me alive.

00:34:12,387 --> 00:34:13,588
STOKES:
Marlon's your guy.

00:34:13,655 --> 00:34:15,323
He's your guy--
just because Hannah wasn't there

00:34:15,390 --> 00:34:16,725
doesn't mean
she didn't help plan this.

00:34:16,791 --> 00:34:19,561
Well, I sure hope it's Marlon,
because he's the one

00:34:19,628 --> 00:34:21,696
we have on trial.

00:34:21,763 --> 00:34:23,832
I stand by the
case we filed.

00:34:23,899 --> 00:34:24,833
I agree.

00:34:24,900 --> 00:34:26,868
The girl's just trying
to protect him.

00:34:27,903 --> 00:34:29,404
Sara?

00:34:34,576 --> 00:34:36,344
This was more about brains
than brawn.

00:34:36,411 --> 00:34:38,246
I think Hannah did it.

00:34:40,315 --> 00:34:42,284
Two out of three.

00:34:42,350 --> 00:34:46,454
In my world,
that's called an acquittal.

00:34:54,696 --> 00:34:55,964
High school.

00:34:56,031 --> 00:34:58,033
Even if you're popular,

00:34:58,099 --> 00:35:01,903
or a jock, or a brain...

00:35:01,970 --> 00:35:04,139
it can be hell.

00:35:04,205 --> 00:35:06,575
Everybody here remembers

00:35:06,641 --> 00:35:08,810
what it was like...

00:35:08,877 --> 00:35:10,779
what it was really like.

00:35:10,845 --> 00:35:12,747
Now take a look

00:35:12,814 --> 00:35:14,316
at Marlon West.

00:35:14,382 --> 00:35:18,353
Take a good, hard look.

00:35:20,055 --> 00:35:21,957
Not popular...

00:35:22,023 --> 00:35:26,061
<i>not a jock... not a brain.</i>

00:35:27,896 --> 00:35:32,667
<i>Now imagine what it must</i>
<i>be like to be Marlon West</i>

00:35:32,734 --> 00:35:36,605
<i>day after day after day</i>

00:35:36,671 --> 00:35:39,574
<i>in the sociological</i>
<i>pressure cooker of high</i>
<i>school.</i>

00:35:39,641 --> 00:35:44,512
<i>This imposing, struggling</i>
<i>outsider like Marlon</i>

00:35:44,579 --> 00:35:46,014
<i>resenting someone</i>

00:35:46,081 --> 00:35:47,415
<i>like Stacy Vollmer,</i>
<i>who made it look</i>

00:35:47,482 --> 00:35:53,421
<i>so easy to be popular,</i>
<i>athletic and smart.</i>

00:35:54,723 --> 00:35:58,860
<i>That strong resentment</i>
<i>was already festering</i>

00:35:58,927 --> 00:36:00,962
<i>when Stacy made</i>
<i>Marlon's sister the object</i>

00:36:01,029 --> 00:36:03,965
<i>of a typical high school prank.</i>

00:36:05,533 --> 00:36:08,703
<i>And that is when Marlon,</i>
<i>his resentment</i>

00:36:08,770 --> 00:36:11,373
boiling over, crossed a line:

00:36:11,439 --> 00:36:15,810
He stalked Stacy.

00:36:15,877 --> 00:36:17,712
You've seen and heard evidence

00:36:17,779 --> 00:36:22,317
illustrating the elaborate pains
he took to rig a shower head

00:36:22,384 --> 00:36:24,519
to torture Stacy,

00:36:24,586 --> 00:36:30,325
<i>how he forced her</i>
<i>to run and fall,</i>

00:36:30,392 --> 00:36:34,029
and watched her die
in a pool of her own blood.

00:36:34,095 --> 00:36:36,831
You know, for the first time
in his life,

00:36:36,898 --> 00:36:37,966
Marlon feels like a hero.

00:36:38,033 --> 00:36:40,835
He's not
invisible anymore.

00:36:40,902 --> 00:36:43,405
He's a killer...

00:36:43,471 --> 00:36:48,009
and he is guilty
beyond all reasonable doubt.

00:36:49,744 --> 00:36:51,813
ALLRED:
"Reasonable doubt."

00:36:51,880 --> 00:36:54,215
You know,
I'm not surprised

00:36:54,282 --> 00:36:56,785
to hear the prosecution
say those words,

00:36:56,851 --> 00:37:01,990
because its case offers nothing
but reasonable doubt.

00:37:02,057 --> 00:37:04,593
<i>Access to sodium?!</i>

00:37:04,659 --> 00:37:06,094
<i>Marlon couldn't find sodium</i>

00:37:06,161 --> 00:37:08,463
<i>on a periodic table</i>
<i>of the elements,</i>

00:37:08,530 --> 00:37:11,299
<i>let alone</i>
<i>a locked supply closet.</i>

00:37:11,366 --> 00:37:14,769
<i>Access to library printers?</i>

00:37:14,836 --> 00:37:18,306
<i>Do you really think</i>
<i>a kid like Marlon</i>

00:37:18,373 --> 00:37:22,777
<i>spends any time in a library?</i>

00:37:22,844 --> 00:37:25,981
<i>The shower head--</i>
<i>yes, Marlon's tall enough.</i>

00:37:26,047 --> 00:37:29,985
<i>He could reach it, but he still</i>
<i>would have had to have handled</i>

00:37:30,051 --> 00:37:35,156
<i>a volatile chemical</i>
<i>with expert safety precautions</i>

00:37:35,223 --> 00:37:39,427
<i>in order to orchestrate</i>
<i>an explosion.</i>

00:37:39,494 --> 00:37:40,829
I mean, ladies
and gentlemen,

00:37:40,895 --> 00:37:42,797
do you know
how to do that?

00:37:42,864 --> 00:37:45,500
I don't know how to do that.

00:37:45,567 --> 00:37:48,336
Right? You'd have to be...

00:37:48,403 --> 00:37:51,339
a genius.

00:37:54,175 --> 00:37:56,244
Marlon?

00:37:56,311 --> 00:37:59,180
Not a genius.

00:37:59,247 --> 00:38:00,448
You know, one
of the underpinnings

00:38:00,515 --> 00:38:03,852
of our justice system
is that it is better

00:38:03,919 --> 00:38:10,825
to send a hundred guilty men
free than to imprison even one

00:38:10,892 --> 00:38:13,662
who's innocent.

00:38:13,728 --> 00:38:18,166
Marlon West
is an innocent man.

00:38:18,233 --> 00:38:25,206
<i>Reasonable doubt compels you</i>
<i>to find him not guilty.</i>

00:38:28,276 --> 00:38:29,311
( <i>phone ringing</i> )

00:38:32,714 --> 00:38:34,883
( <i>second phone starts ringing</i> )

00:38:53,235 --> 00:38:54,636
Defendant shall rise.

00:38:56,838 --> 00:38:58,506
Madam Foreman,

00:38:58,573 --> 00:39:00,141
what is the jury's verdict?

00:39:00,208 --> 00:39:02,544
FOREMAN:
On the sole count
of murder in the first degree,

00:39:02,611 --> 00:39:04,946
we, the jury, find
the defendant, Marlon West...

00:39:05,013 --> 00:39:06,681
not guilty.

00:39:12,254 --> 00:39:13,788
( <i>sobbing</i> )
JUDGE:
So noted.

00:39:13,855 --> 00:39:16,157
Court orders the defendant
released from custody.

00:39:16,224 --> 00:39:17,726
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

00:39:17,792 --> 00:39:19,160
thank you
for your service.

00:39:19,227 --> 00:39:20,528
Court is adjourned.

00:39:20,595 --> 00:39:22,197
( <i>gavel bangs</i> )

00:39:51,059 --> 00:39:53,428
OFFICER:
Sign here.

00:39:59,601 --> 00:40:01,269
Hey, there.

00:40:01,336 --> 00:40:03,338
Did you come
to say bye?

00:40:03,405 --> 00:40:06,107
No. Actually, you and I
are going to be seeing

00:40:06,174 --> 00:40:07,108
a lot of each other.

00:40:07,175 --> 00:40:09,044
If you thought
the DA wouldn't prosecute

00:40:09,110 --> 00:40:11,513
a 12-year-old for murder,
you were wrong.

00:40:11,580 --> 00:40:13,949
He wants justice for Stacy
and her family.

00:40:14,015 --> 00:40:17,185
Of course.
He's a totally linear thinker.

00:40:17,252 --> 00:40:18,920
Most of you guys are.

00:40:18,987 --> 00:40:21,022
Shame on you,
Ms. Sidle.

00:40:21,089 --> 00:40:22,023
Come on, Hannah.

00:40:22,090 --> 00:40:23,625
You don't need
to listen to this.

00:40:23,692 --> 00:40:26,227
Mom, just give us a second.

00:40:33,335 --> 00:40:35,136
You were saying?

00:40:37,739 --> 00:40:38,740
Here.

00:40:44,846 --> 00:40:46,715
( <i>sighs</i> )

00:40:46,781 --> 00:40:49,050
Hannah, with your gifts,

00:40:49,117 --> 00:40:51,286
you could've done
anything you wanted,

00:40:51,353 --> 00:40:53,455
and you picked murder.

00:40:53,521 --> 00:40:55,523
You can't take
that back.

00:40:56,558 --> 00:40:58,893
You're worried
how I'm going turn out.

00:40:58,960 --> 00:41:00,495
Of course I am.

00:41:00,562 --> 00:41:02,664
I know it seems
like a really long time,

00:41:02,731 --> 00:41:05,166
but... in five years,

00:41:05,233 --> 00:41:08,136
the Stacies of the world
would've been behind you.

00:41:09,170 --> 00:41:10,505
Let me guess.

00:41:10,572 --> 00:41:12,173
You were a smart kid in school.

00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:14,976
Maybe you feel
we're a little bit alike.

00:41:15,043 --> 00:41:17,279
There aren't many people
like you.

00:41:17,345 --> 00:41:20,248
That's what my parents
always say, too.

00:41:21,249 --> 00:41:24,185
The last four months,
all they cared about

00:41:24,252 --> 00:41:28,623
was the effect of the trial
on me... not Marlon.

00:41:28,690 --> 00:41:30,692
It's been that way

00:41:30,759 --> 00:41:32,527
ever since I was 14 months old

00:41:32,594 --> 00:41:35,363
and started spelling words
with plastic letters.

00:41:35,430 --> 00:41:38,700
It's so unfair,
and nobody ever sees it.

00:41:40,735 --> 00:41:42,804
He doesn't deserve
to go to jail.

00:41:44,873 --> 00:41:49,411
If I get convicted,
what's the worst-case scenario?

00:41:49,477 --> 00:41:51,212
I mean, I'll be out
in five years

00:41:51,279 --> 00:41:53,348
with an undergraduate
degree.

00:41:53,415 --> 00:41:55,817
There's no "Son of Sam" law
in Nevada--

00:41:55,884 --> 00:41:57,652
that was ruled
unconstitutional--

00:41:57,719 --> 00:42:00,422
so I'm free to write a book
about all this.

00:42:01,456 --> 00:42:03,224
The story'll
be worth millions.

00:42:03,291 --> 00:42:05,994
Freaks are always
good box office.

00:42:06,061 --> 00:42:08,163
You're not a freak.

00:42:08,229 --> 00:42:10,999
When's the last time
you had to sit down

00:42:11,066 --> 00:42:13,735
to be eye-level with a murder
suspect who was standing up?

00:42:13,802 --> 00:42:15,804
Hannah, you are smart.

00:42:15,870 --> 00:42:17,672
So I've been told.

00:42:17,739 --> 00:42:19,507
But you're not smart enough
to get away with murder.

00:42:19,574 --> 00:42:21,176
I think I am.

00:42:21,243 --> 00:42:22,677
A lot of people
are smart enough

00:42:22,744 --> 00:42:24,045
to get away with murder.

00:42:24,112 --> 00:42:26,114
You probably are, too.

00:42:26,181 --> 00:42:28,183
But you have to be really smart

00:42:28,250 --> 00:42:31,786
to make people think things
happened that never did.

00:42:32,821 --> 00:42:35,790
What do you mean, exactly?

00:42:35,857 --> 00:42:37,025
Please don't worry about me.

00:42:37,092 --> 00:42:39,194
I'm going to be fine.

00:42:43,765 --> 00:42:46,701
( <i>whispering</i> ):
I didn't kill Stacy.

00:42:46,768 --> 00:42:48,404
Marlon did.

